tual present that depletes the future and erodes our grasp of the past?Beginning its examination around 1900, when rapid modernization was accompanied by comparably intense reflection on changing temporal experience, Precarious Times provides historical depth and perspective to current debates on the "digital now." Expanding the modern discourse on time and speed, Fuchs deploys such concepts as attention, slowness and lateness to emphasize the uneven quality of time around the world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aAnxiety in art. 0aAnxiety in literature. 0aArts and societyzGermanyxHistoryy20th century. 0aArts and societyzGermanyxHistoryy21st century. 0aGerman literaturey20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aGerman literaturey20th centuryxThemes, motives. 0aGerman literaturey21st centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aGerman literaturey21st centuryxThemes, motives. 0aMotion pictureszGermanyxHistory. 0aTime and photography. 0aTime in art. 0aTime in literature. 0aTime in motion pictures. 4aCultural Studies. 4aLiterary Studies. 4aPhilosophy.  aModern time regime, temporal anxiety, acceleration, precariousness, speed culture.  amodernism, contemporary German literature.  aslowness, lateness, attention, presentism, digital now, Eigenzeit, photography, film.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065198008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Stud. 2019 Englishz978311061036908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and 